36:07.998 --> 36:10.701
(Betty gasping)

36:23.914 --> 36:26.784
(birds chirping)

36:32.422 --> 36:33.457
- Here.

36:33.490 --> 36:34.925
- I'm okay.

36:34.958 --> 36:36.493
- I didn't say you weren't.

36:36.526 --> 36:40.564
- Just, I'm done with
being tired, I'm done.

36:40.597 --> 36:41.532
- You're done?

36:41.565 --> 36:42.967
- I'm done.

36:43.000 --> 36:44.802
- This exactly what I
said was gonna happen.

36:44.835 --> 36:47.571
Now I'm gonna have to carry
you back down the hill,

36:47.604 --> 36:49.340
just like last time.

36:50.340 --> 36:53.611
- You know what this
weather reminds me of?

36:53.644 --> 36:56.513
- The wife and kids you
left back in Sydney.

36:56.546 --> 36:57.648
"Dante's Inferno?"

36:57.681 --> 36:59.817
No, no, your rational fear of
fire ants.

36:59.850 --> 37:04.488
- There's nothing irrational
about fearing fire ants.

37:04.521 --> 37:05.189
- Well?

37:05.222 --> 37:07.458
- No, I'm done talking to you.

37:07.491 --> 37:09.560
- Okay, I wanna know, I wanna
know.

37:09.593 --> 37:11.662
No, you're being a sarcastic
asshole.

37:11.695 --> 37:13.030
- I know.

37:13.063 --> 37:14.999
Don't you love me for who I am.

37:15.032 --> 37:16.900
- You get enough love from
yourself.

37:16.933 --> 37:17.868
(birds chirping)

37:17.901 --> 37:19.270
- Ouch.

37:19.303 --> 37:20.771
Finally comes out,

37:20.804 --> 37:22.773
the truth of how you really
feel.

37:22.806 --> 37:23.807
Well, I beg to differ.

37:23.841 --> 37:27.077
- For once we have a
European summer, you know.

37:27.110 --> 37:29.580
It's warm, but not too hard.

37:31.014 --> 37:34.685
Like the forest could just
open up onto the Mediterranean.

37:34.718 --> 37:36.787
- Yeah, it beautiful.

37:36.820 --> 37:38.389
- Yeah.

37:38.422 --> 37:40.491
Gosh, I'd do anything to go
swimming

37:40.524 --> 37:43.527
in that blue, blue water again.

37:43.560 --> 37:45.629
- I mean, the temperature's
a bit like it was.

37:45.662 --> 37:49.767
That doesn't exactly look like
we're in Mykonos or Positano,

37:49.800 --> 37:52.069
but I'm pretty happy about that.

37:52.102 --> 37:54.104
I mean, don't take offense,

37:54.137 --> 37:57.841
I'd rather be nowhere else in
the world.

37:57.874 --> 37:59.310
But now is a good a
time as any to tell you,

37:59.343 --> 38:02.780
but I really didn't like that
trip.

38:02.813 --> 38:04.848
- You're just bitter about the
last week.

38:04.881 --> 38:06.850
- I'm bitter I had to
isolate from you, yeah,

38:06.883 --> 38:08.452
but that's not it.

38:10.721 --> 38:12.523
- Mark, you're the one that got
sick.

38:12.556 --> 38:13.724
- Oh, we were both sick.

38:13.757 --> 38:17.961
Look, it's not that, it's
just, I just don't like Europe.

38:17.994 --> 38:20.964
- It's a pretty big continent to
resent.

38:20.997 --> 38:25.769
- Well, it's just so dirty,
all right and crowded.

38:25.802 --> 38:27.471
Oh, do you remember Rome, hmm?

38:27.504 --> 38:28.706
Do you remember the day
you met up with Lily

38:28.739 --> 38:30.441
and I was left to explore alone?

38:30.474 --> 38:32.009
- Yeah, the day you got sick.

38:32.042 --> 38:33.911
- Yeah, I got heat stroke, okay

38:33.944 --> 38:36.146
'cause the weather was
just like this, but hotter.

38:36.179 --> 38:37.581
And we'd seen all the sites,

38:37.614 --> 38:40.084
and so I was just
walking around this city,

38:40.117 --> 38:42.553
taking in the concrete and the
crowds.

38:42.586 --> 38:43.621
And then I got lost.

38:43.654 --> 38:45.356
- Mark, you were sick
'cause you got blind drunk

38:45.389 --> 38:46.056
the night before.

38:46.089 --> 38:46.924
- What?

38:46.957 --> 38:47.892
No.

38:47.925 --> 38:50.494
Well, yes, but that's not the
point okay.

38:50.527 --> 38:53.130
I got lost and I ended
up outside the Rome Zoo,

38:53.163 --> 38:56.166
this bio park or something,
anyway,

38:56.199 --> 38:58.702
I decided to kill some time to
go on in,

38:58.735 --> 39:00.371
maybe it was to get out of the
sun.

39:00.404 --> 39:02.106
I don't know.
- That was your mistake.

39:02.139 --> 39:05.909
- Yeah, well look, I went in
there and that was just awful.

39:05.942 --> 39:07.111
I mean, you'd think places like
that

39:07.144 --> 39:09.079
were outlawed 50 years ago.

39:09.112 --> 39:11.615
Okay, the elephant
enclosure, it had no shade.

39:11.648 --> 39:12.916
So all of them were just pressed
up

39:12.950 --> 39:16.053
against the side of a clay
building, clinging to its
shadow.

39:16.086 --> 39:17.454
And they had wolves all right,

39:17.487 --> 39:19.022
fucking timber wolves in that
heat.

39:19.055 --> 39:21.959
And they were either all
passed out or sedated.

39:21.992 --> 39:24.995
I mean, and the hippo, my God,
that hippo,

39:25.028 --> 39:27.798
he was in an enclosure
the size of our apartment.

39:27.831 --> 39:29.566
The concrete ground of
the pool at its sense,

39:29.599 --> 39:32.636
that was barely the hippo's
length.

39:32.669 --> 39:35.806
Oh my God that fucking hippo.

39:35.839 --> 39:39.710
- So you are basing your whole
judgment of a whole continent

39:39.743 --> 39:42.112
of one trip to a zoo?

39:42.145 --> 39:43.113
- Yeah.

39:43.146 --> 39:46.517
Because Europe made me
feel like that hippo.

39:46.550 --> 39:50.454
- Are you honestly incapable
of enjoying anything?

39:50.487 --> 39:52.823
(birds chirping)

39:52.856 --> 39:54.024
- I think so.

39:54.057 --> 39:56.927
(birds chirping)

39:59.963 --> 40:01.899
I think I'm feeling it.

40:03.033 --> 40:04.635
- What's that?

40:04.668 --> 40:06.070
- It's hitting me.

40:08.038 --> 40:09.106
- The acid,

40:09.139 --> 40:10.674
I almost forgot.

40:10.707 --> 40:12.910
- Are you feeling anything?

40:17.214 --> 40:18.682
- Yeah, I think a smidge.

40:18.715 --> 40:20.050
- Yeah.

40:20.083 --> 40:24.021
- How broccoli of the trees
right now?

40:24.054 --> 40:25.556
- About a six.

40:25.589 --> 40:26.690
(both laughing)

40:26.723 --> 40:28.625
- We're getting there.

40:28.658 --> 40:30.894
Nearly, nearly, nearly.

